      About this item

      • Includes: 1-diva smart ELV+ dimmer switch, coordinating wall plate purchased separately
      • Caseta's newest aesthetic: features the recognized, well-loved design of Lutron diva LED+ dimmers, and matches existing paddle style dimmers and switches for a classic look throughout any home
      • Works in nearly any residential application including MLV/ELV loads: add smart lighting control to undercabinet and track lights, tape lights, toe kicks and other accent lighting that has MLV/ELV loads
      • Superior dimming : Works with LED, incandescent, halogen, ELV and MLV lights in single pole, 3-way and multi-location applications (up to 10 pico remotes or claro smart accessory switches)
      • Easy installation and setup: Install the diva smart ELV+ dimmer switch in as little as 15-minutes, neutral wire required
      • Precise dimming: The soft-glow light bar and slider provide easy and precise control from the wall, preset allows you to turn on your lights to your preferred predetermined level
      • Add a 2nd switch almost anywhere: Create a 3-way with your diva smart ELV+ dimmer switch by mounting a pico paddle remote (PJ2-P2B-GWH)/wall mount bracket to almost any wall surface (both sold separately), can be used with a claro smart accessory switch (DVRF-AS-WH) or a mechanical switch
      • Why a smart hub: The smart hub provides an ultra-reliable and responsive local network for your lighting system, simple setup with a single button press and works even when your Wi-Fi goes down
      • Most connected: Caseta connects with more leading smart home devices - including Alexa, Apple Home, Google Home, ring and Sonos - than any other smart lighting control brand (smart hub required, sold separately)
      • Control your way: Caseta puts the smarts in the switch, so you can control your lights a variety of ways - via the Lutron app, with your voice, at the switch, or with a Pico smart remote (smart hub, sold separately, required for app or voice control)

      Product Description

      Experience the best smart lighting experience with Lutron and the recognized aesthetic of the Diva smart ELV+ dimmer for Caseta lighting. Featuring the well-loved design of the Lutron Diva LED+ dimmer, unlock smart lighting for nearly any residential application including MLV/ELV loads. Add smart lighting control to undercabinet and track lights, tape lights, toe kicks and other accent lights. Easily install the Diva Smart ELV+ in as little as 15-minutes and set up the trim and phase control with a press of the button or using the Lutron app. Use the Diva Smart ELV+ in a 3-way using the matching Pico Paddle Remote (PJ2-P2B-GWH sold separately), Claro smart accessory switch, or a mechanical switch. If you want to control the load from more than 2-locations, use Pico remotes to unlock control at up to 10 different locations. The Diva smart ELV+ dimmer is a great solution for LED fixtures with integrated, built-in drivers, ELV track lights and problem LEDs that may prefer a reverse phase dimmer. The dimmer is also capable of controlling 250-Watt dimmable LED, 500-Watt incandescent/halogen/ELV, and 400-Watt MLV. Diva smart ELV+ dimmer, the most capable smart lighting control for nearly any residential light. Please note, coordinating wall plate for dimmer is sold separately.

        5.0 out of 5 stars Pricey, but a solid solution for retrofit of existing low voltage lighting
        Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2024
        Color: WhiteVerified Purchase
        In the past 6 weeks I've purchased more the $2k in Caseta switches etc as I work to replace an aging home automation system. The Caseta ELV+ have worked well to manage an array of low voltage transformer controls, new and old. The documentation in the box is very basic and does not address many of the features this switch offers, and for some reason Lutron does a good job hiding the complete documentation deep in their website and embedded in a document that attempts to cover all of the other switch products at the same time. A simple QR code that goes directly to this products manual would go a long way toward my initial experience. That said they do work well, even with low voltage halogen bulbs, just be sure and add up your bulb wattage and don't exceed 250W. Set up is simple (with proper manuals) and the switches and covers have a quality look and feel. The ELV+ are a great solution for LV transformer control, but they are pricey!!.
